### Tested versions

4.4.stable

### System information

Windows 11 - Godot v4.4.stable - Vulkan (Forward+) - Nvidia RTX 3050Ti

### Issue description

When UV of some face of a mesh is rotated then Heightmap of material won't work properly. Actually I'm not sure is this an issue or not.

Here's a video: https://youtu.be/9GZUqEysneE

### Steps to reproduce

1. Create a script `some_script_name.gd` and create a node with this script in a scene.
```gdscript
@tool
extends MeshInstance3D

@export_range(0.0, 360.0, 0.1)
var rotate_uv = 0.0:
	get: return rotate_uv;
	set(value):
		rotate_uv = value;

@export_tool_button("Regenerate Mesh")
var regenerate_mesh_button = func():
	regenerate_mesh();

func regenerate_mesh():
	var mesh_arrays := PlaneMesh.new().get_mesh_arrays();

	var vertices := mesh_arrays[Mesh.ARRAY_VERTEX] as PackedVector3Array;
	var indices := mesh_arrays[Mesh.ARRAY_INDEX] as PackedInt32Array;
	var normals := mesh_arrays[Mesh.ARRAY_NORMAL] as PackedVector3Array;
	var uvs := mesh_arrays[Mesh.ARRAY_TEX_UV] as PackedVector2Array;

	var surface_tool = SurfaceTool.new();

	surface_tool.begin(Mesh.PRIMITIVE_TRIANGLES);

	var index := 0;
	for vertex in vertices:
		surface_tool.set_normal(normals[index]);
		var uv = Transform2D.IDENTITY.rotated(deg_to_rad(rotate_uv)) * uvs[index];
		surface_tool.set_uv(uv);
		surface_tool.add_vertex(vertices[index]);
		index += 1;

	for i in range(indices.size()):
		surface_tool.add_index(indices[i]);

	mesh = surface_tool.commit();
```
2. Assign a material with heightmap in `Geometry -> Material Override`
3. Tweak `Rotate UV` in the inspector and click `Regenerate mesh`

