### Tested versions

4.4.stable

### System information

Godot v4.4.stable - Windows 10 (build 19045) - Multi-window, 2 monitors - Vulkan (Forward+) - dedicated NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3060 Ti (NVIDIA; 32.0.15.7270) - Intel(R) Core(TM) i7-6700K CPU @ 4.00GHz (8 threads)

### Issue description

Currently when in fullscreen and setting window mode to windowed, Godot will restore window's previous position. However, it takes no measures to make sure the remembered rect is within visible area.
```cpp
if (wd.pre_fs_valid) {
    rect = wd.pre_fs_rect;
}
```
This is in comparison to how Godot validates the rect on startup or when calling `window_set_current_screen`
```cpp
Rect2i srect = screen_get_usable_rect(rq_screen);
Point2i wpos = p_rect.position;
if (srect != Rect2i()) {
    wpos = wpos.clamp(srect.position, srect.position + srect.size - p_rect.size / 3);
}
```
So I'd guess the solution would be to do something similar when leaving fullscreen
```cpp
if (wd.pre_fs_valid) {
    rect = wd.pre_fs_rect;

    Point2i wpos = {rect.left, rect.top};
    const Point2i wsize = {rect.right - rect.left, rect.bottom - rect.top};
    const Rect2i wrect = {wpos, wsize};

    int screen = get_screen_from_rect(wrect);
    if (screen < 0) {
        screen = get_primary_screen();
    }

    const Rect2i srect = screen_get_usable_rect(screen);
    if (srect != Rect2i()) {
        wpos = wpos.clamp(srect.position, srect.position + srect.size - wsize / 3);
    }

    rect.left = wpos.x;
    rect.top = wpos.y;
}
```

### Steps to reproduce

1. Put a window on a second monitor
2. Set fullscreen mode
3. Change current monitor by calling window_set_current_screen(0)
4. Turn off second monitor
5. Set windowed mode
6. Godot will put your window offscreen

